---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Privacy policy"
    description="What data the LSCSS documentation site collects, how Umami analytics is used, and your rights."
>
    <main class="page-shell">
        <section class="site-hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">Site policy</p>

            <h1>Privacy policy</h1>

            <p class="intro">
                This policy describes how the LSCSS documentation site at
                <strong>lscss.crayonsandco.de</strong> handles information. The site is
                operated by <a href="https://crayonsandco.de/">Crayons and Code</a>
                (Phil Steer). We keep collection to a minimum: there are no accounts,
                newsletters, or comment forms on this site.
            </p>

            <p class="intro">
                <small>Last updated: {lastUpdated}.</small>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>What we collect</h2>
            <h3>Analytics (production only)</h3>
            <p>
                On the live site we use
                <a href="https://umami.is/">Umami Cloud</a>, a privacy-focused analytics
                service. Umami is <strong>cookieless</strong> for visitors: it does not set
                advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. It records aggregated data such
                as:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Pages viewed and when</li>
                <li>Referring site (if the browser sends it)</li>
                <li>Browser, operating system, and device type (from the user agent)</li>
                <li>General location derived from the connection (typically country or region)</li>
                <li>Screen size band (for layout statistics)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Umami does not collect names, email addresses, or payment details on this
                site. We do not sell analytics data. The tracker is not loaded during local
                development builds. Collect requests are sent to
                <code>cloud.umami.is</code> as described in our
                <a href="/cookies/">cookie and storage policy</a>.
            </p>
            <p>
                For how Umami processes data as a processor, see
                <a href="https://umami.is/privacy">Umami’s privacy policy</a>.
            </p>

            <h3>What we do not collect on this site</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Account registrations or login data (there is no login)</li>
                <li>Form submissions via this domain (contact is through Crayons and Code separately)</li>
                <li>Payment or billing information</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Why we use analytics</h2>
            <p>
                We use Umami to understand which documentation pages are useful, whether
                navigation is working, and how much traffic the site receives. The lawful
                basis under UK GDPR is <strong>legitimate interest</strong> in operating
                and improving a public documentation site, balanced against minimal
                collection and no profiling for advertising.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Storage on your device</h2>
            <p>
                Browser storage used by this site (theme preference and similar) is
                explained on the <a href="/cookies/">cookie and storage policy</a> page.
                That is separate from Umami analytics.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Third parties</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Umami Cloud</strong> — analytics processing as above.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Hosting and CDN</strong> — the site is served through our
                    hosting provider, which will process connection data (IP address,
                    request logs) as part of delivering pages. Retention and security are
                    governed by that provider’s terms.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Fonts used on this site are self-hosted; page views do not trigger
                third-party font requests.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Retention</h2>
            <p>
                Analytics retention is controlled in Umami Cloud (typically months, not
                years). Hosting logs depend on the provider. If you contact us about
                accessibility or other site issues, we keep correspondence only as long
                as needed to handle the request.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Your rights</h2>
            <p>
                If UK or EEA data protection law applies to you, you may have rights to
                access, rectify, erase, restrict, or object to processing, and to lodge a
                complaint with the ICO (UK) or your local supervisory authority. Because
                Umami does not identify you by name on this site, we may not be able to
                isolate a single visit as “your” record without additional information you
                provide voluntarily.
            </p>
            <p>
                To exercise rights or ask questions, contact
                <a href="https://crayonsandco.de/">Crayons and Code</a>.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Changes</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this policy when the site or analytics setup changes. The
                “Last updated” date at the top will change when we do.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Related policies</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/cookies/">Cookie and storage policy</a></li>
                <li><a href="/accessibility/">Accessibility statement</a></li>
                <li><a href="/ai/">AI and this site</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
